[h1]GK Raiding Expanded[/h1]

Steal their people. Strip their planets. Fund your own pirate enclave.

[b]Stellaris 4.3.0[/b]

[hr][/hr]

[h2]Pop Raiding[/h2]

Raiding forces capture enemy pops through bombardment and invasion. How many you can take is limited, but spending Influence authorizes deeper raids. Each escalation takes more, costs more, and draws galactic attention.

When a tier is filled, choose how to proceed: push deeper, hold position, switch to resource pillaging, demand tribute, or negotiate policy changes from the defender. All of these end pop raiding against the target but the war continues.

Four war goals shape how you raid. [b]Plunder[/b] takes any pops. [b]Emancipation[/b] targets the enslaved. [b]Reaping[/b] removes all limits and denies the enemy any chance to surrender. With the [b]Robots Only[/b] policy, emancipation wars can target synthetic rights instead.

[h2]Pillaging[/h2]

Devastation dealt to enemy colonies generates resources based on what they actually produce. Invading colonies cashes out whatever is left. Declaring a [b]Pillage[/b] war increases the yield and guarantees tribute on surrender.

Pillage Yield stacks from multiple sources: base, traditions, civics, and the Pillage war goal. Higher yield means more resources per devastation and harsher penalties on the worlds you strip. Occupied planets are automatically raided each month, with captured pops split among allied armies.

[h2]Civics[/h2]

[b]Emancipators[/b] and [b]Liberation Enterprise[/b] wage war to free the enslaved. [b]Harvest Incorporated[/b] treats conquered populations as corporate assets. [b]Harvesting Protocol[/b] abducts organics to feed a machine intelligence's power grid, starting with its own battery species.

[b]Hive Bodysnatcher[/b] gains pop raiding access, the raiding bombardment stance, and the Reaping war goal.

[h2]Reaping[/h2]

Reaping is a raiding focus policy, not always available. Only Barbaric Despoiler civics and Hive Bodysnatcher with Xenophobe ethics (or gestalt empires) can select it. Declaring a Reaping war carries a severe galaxy-wide opinion penalty that takes decades to decay.

Nihilistic Acquisition empires use the Influence escalation system to reach full depopulation instead.

[h2]Despoliation Traditions[/h2]

Adopting the Despoliation tree unlocks resource pillaging and the Pillage war goal for any empire, along with +1 Pillage Yield for empires that already have native pillaging access. Completing the tree grants an Ascension Perk slot and unlocks the Privateer Enclave.

[h2]Privateer Enclave[/h2]

Found your own pirate haven. It raids autonomously, shakes down its victims for tribute, and pays you dividends. Its salvager crews pick through the wreckage of battle for alloys, minerals, and rare materials. Upgrade it to expand its fleet, increase raid frequency, and unlock richer payouts. Each enclave develops its own personality at founding. Build a Smuggler's Port on your starbases for additional trade value. Convert freely between mercenary and privateer enclaves through the diplomacy menu.

[hr][/hr]

[h3]DLC Support[/h3]

Most core features function without DLCs.
They are required for the following additional features:
[list]
[*][b]Overlord[/b]: Privateer Enclave
[*][b]Grand Archive[/b]: Enclave specimens and Boarding Cables tradition variant
[*][b]Paragon[/b]: Recovery Fleets council agenda
[/list]

[h3]Compatibility[/h3]

Should be compatible with most mods. Full overwrites:
[list]
[*]Bombardment stance: [i]raiding[/i]
[*]War goals: [i]wg_plunder[/i], [i]wg_plunder_raid[/i]
[*]Casus belli: [i]cb_despoliation[/i], [i]cb_pirate_raid[/i]
[*]Game rules: [i]can_orbital_bombard[/i], [i]can_spawn_debris[/i]
[*]Scripted triggers: [i]is_unfriendly[/i], [i]is_slaver[/i], [i]prefers_commander_governors[/i], [i]has_murderous_civic_or_origin[/i]
[*]Policies: [i]debris[/i]
[*]Economic categories: [i]planet_livestock_farmers[/i], [i]planet_livestock_miners[/i], [i]planet_livestock_metallurgists[/i], [i]pop_category_purge[/i], [i]planet_organic_batteries[/i]
[*]Events: [i]enclave.2[/i], [i]enclave.205[/i]
[/list]

